{
  "markdown": "[Skip to content](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/#VPContent)

On this page

# useFetch [â€‹](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/\#usefetch)

Category

[Network](https://vueuse.org/functions#category=Network)

Export Size

2.28 kB

Last Changed

3 months ago

Reactive [Fetch API](https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/API/Fetch_API) provides the ability to abort requests, intercept requests before they are fired, automatically refetch requests when the url changes, and create your own [`useFetch`](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/) with predefined options.

[Learn useFetch with this FREE video lesson from Vue School!](https://vueschool.io/lessons/vueuse-utilities-usefetch-and-reactify?friend=vueuse)

TIP

When using with Nuxt 3, this function will **NOT** be auto imported in favor of Nuxt's built-in [`useFetch()`](https://v3.nuxtjs.org/api/composables/use-fetch). Use explicit import if you want to use the function from VueUse.

## Demo [â€‹](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/\#demo)

[source](https://github.com/vueuse/vueuse/blob/main/packages/core/useFetch/demo.vue) [playground (beta)](https://playground.vueuse.org/?vueuse=14.0.0-beta.1#)

The following URLs can be used to test different features of useFetch

Normal Request: ` https://httpbin.org/get `

Abort Request: ` https://httpbin.org/delay/10 `

Response Error: ` http://httpbin.org/status/500 `

Execute Refetch Off

```
isFinished: true
isFetching: false
canAbort: false
statusCode: null
error: Failed to fetch
data: null

```

## Usage [â€‹](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/\#usage)

### Basic Usage [â€‹](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/\#basic-usage)

The [`useFetch`](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/) function can be used by simply providing a url. The url can be either a string or a `ref`. The `data` object will contain the result of the request, the `error` object will contain any errors, and the `isFetching` object will indicate if the request is loading.

ts

```
import {
