[`useFetch`](https://vueuse.org/core/useFetch/) can also be awaited just like a normal fetch. Note that whenever a component is asynchronous, whatever component that uses it must wrap the component in a `<Suspense>` tag. You can read more about the suspense api in the [Official Vue 3 Docs](https://vuejs.org/guide/built-ins/suspense.html)

